headline: Labour Codes trigger showdown, Unions call ‘combative resistance’ on Nov 26
synthesis: This ties into broader market movement and sentiment.

timeline.text: The upcoming showdown on November 26 highlights the escalating tensions between labor unions and regulatory bodies over the new Labour Codes. This combative resistance reflects broader market sentiments, as stakeholders are increasingly concerned about the implications for worker rights and economic stability. Observers will be watching closely to see how this confrontation unfolds and its potential impact on labor relations moving forward.
